Subject: Granulomatous prostatitis 
To: Abigail
Content:
Granulomatous prostatitis is an uncommon disease of the prostate, an exocrine gland of the male reproductive system. It is a form of prostatitis, i.e. inflammation of the prostate, resulting from infection (bacterial, viral, or fungal), the BCG therapy, malacoplakia or systemic granulomatous diseases which involve the prostate. Pathogenesis of Granulomatous Prostatitis: Prostatic secretions escape into the stroma and elicit an inflammatory response. Histopathology Noticeable destruction of Acini, surrounded by epitheloid cells, giant cells, lymphocytes, plasma cells + dense fibrosis. Pathogenesis Histopathology 
I read the paragraph on http://wikipedia.org
